<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,844,1190]" box="[264,383,844,869]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[264,383,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,844,1190]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Body length up to 
<quantity box="[535,622,884,910]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
. Antennae 1 as long as head and first pereonite; flagellum oval, distal margin rounded. Gnathopod 2; carpal process about half­length propodus. Pereopods 3 &amp; 4; dactylus relatively short, length about 0.2x propodus. Pereopods 5 &amp; 6; dactylus length slightly more than 0.1x propodus. Pereopod 7; basis rectangular, width about 0.8x length, slightly longer than ischium to carpus combined, with slight rounded posterodistal lobe barely overlapping ischium. Lateral corners of last urosomite not produced. Uropod 3; peduncle distinctly longer than rami; sexual dimorphism of endopod not evident. Telson semi­circular, length almost half peduncle of U3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1244,1670]" box="[264,366,1244,1269]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1244,1670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This species most closely resembles 
<emphasis box="[747,905,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing, 1888: 1279 -" authorityYear="1283" box="[747,901,1284,1309]" class="Malacostraca" family="Vibiliidae" genus="Vibilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="propinqua">V. propinqua</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and perhaps also 
<emphasis box="[1119,1249,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bovallius" authorityYear="1887" box="[1119,1245,1284,1309]" class="Malacostraca" family="Vibiliidae" genus="Vibilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbosa">V. gibbosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but is readily distinguished by the relatively short dactylus of the pereopods, particularly pereopods 5 and 6, and by the rounded telson.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1244,1670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1845" box="[312,535,1404,1429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Vibiliidae" genus="Vibilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeangerardi">
<emphasis box="[312,535,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Vibilia jeangerardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a well­known associate of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Madin &amp; Harbison" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[890,1058,1404,1429]" class="Thaliacea" family="Salpidae" genus="Salpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Salpida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis box="[890,1058,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Salpa maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marion, A. F." box="[1074,1233,1404,1430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref38038" refString="Marion, A. F. (1874) Recherches sur les animaux inferieurs du golfe de Marseille. Descriptions des Crustaces Amphipodes parasites des salpes. Annales des Sciences naturelles (Tome 1), sixieme serie. Zoologie et Paleontologie, serie 5, 17, 1 - 19, pls 1, 2." type="book chapter" year="1874">Marion 1874</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Harbison, G. R. &amp; Biggs, D. C. &amp; Madin, L. P." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="465 - 488" refId="ref36924" refString="Harbison, G. R., Biggs, D. C. &amp; Madin, L. P. (1977) The associations of Amphipoda Hyperiidea with gelatinous zooplankton - II. Associations with Cnidaria, Ctenophora and Radiolaria. Deep-Sea Research, 24, 465 - 488." type="journal article" year="1977">Madin &amp; Harbison 1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Laval, P." box="[482,619,1444,1470]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="11 - 56" refId="ref37656" refString="Laval, P. (1980) Hyperiid amphipods as crustacean parasitoids associated with gelatinous plankton. Oceanography and Marine Biology, Annual Review, 18, 11 - 56." type="journal article" year="1980">Laval 1980</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1244,1670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The publication date for this species is not clear from the literature with some authors referring it to 1849, which is the date of the title page of the work, while others quote 1845 (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovallius, C." box="[327,524,1564,1590]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref35551" refString="Bovallius, C. (1887 c) Contributions to a monograph of the Amphipoda Hyperiidea, Part I: 1. The families Tyronidae, Lanceolidae and Vibilidae. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 21 (5), 1 - 72, pls 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1887">Bovallius 1887c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, M. E. &amp; Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N." box="[539,823,1564,1590]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref40377" refString="Vinogradov, M. E., Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N. (1982) Amfipody-Giperiidy (Amphipoda: Hyperiidea) Mrovogo Okeanea. Akademiya Nauk SSSR, Opredeliteli po Faune SSSR No. 132. Leningrad, 492 pp. [In Russian]. (English translation, 1996, Smithsonian Institution Libraries, Washington D. C., D. Siegel-Causey, Scientific Editor)." type="book" year="1982">
Vinogradov 
<emphasis box="[688,742,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. 1982
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Sherborn, C. D. &amp; Woodward, B. B." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="161 - 164" refId="ref38880" refString="Sherborn, C. D. &amp; Woodward, B. B. (1901) Dates of publication of the Zoological and Botanical portions of some French Voyages - Part II. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 7 (8), 161 - 164." type="journal article" year="1901">Sherborn and Woodward (1901)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodward, B. B." box="[405,624,1604,1630]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref40797" refString="Woodward, B. B. (1904) Catalogue of the books, manuscripts, maps and drawings in the British Museum (Natural History). Vol. II. E - K. British Museum (Natural History), London." type="book" year="1904">Woodward (1904)</bibRefCitation>
, that part of the work by Lucas describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1845" box="[1153,1322,1604,1629]" class="Malacostraca" family="Vibiliidae" genus="Vibilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeangerardi">
<emphasis box="[1153,1322,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">V. jeangerardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was actually published in 1846.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1724,1870]" box="[264,407,1724,1749]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[264,407,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1724,1870]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This species is most common in the Mediterranean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean but, has also been recorded from the Indian Ocean, northeast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1030,1171,1804,1830]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stephensen, K." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref39468" refString="Stephensen, K. (1918) Hyperiidea-Amphipoda (Lanceolidae, Scinidae, Vibiliidae, Thaumatopsidae). Report on the Danish Oceanographical Expeditions 1908 - 10 to the Mediterranean and Adjacent Seas, 2 (Biology - D 2), 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1918">Stephensen 1918</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
